Conclusion
Analysis shows that while desktop performance is stable, mobile performance is significantly lagging due to high LCP and TTI. The primary bottlenecks are not optimized images, heavy JavaScript, and slow-loading page elements. Addressing these issues especially on mobile can substantially improve overall user experience and performance scores.

